      "message": "Hello @eakammer@google.com,\n\n@pirama@google.com mentioned the following in the other long comment:\n\n\u003e The convention is to set rpath to `$ORIGIN:$ORIGIN/../lib` and install libc++ to `\u003cinstall-bin-dir\u003e/../lib`.\n\u003e\n\u003e -static will produce a static binary - which is not what you want. Use -static-libstdc++ flag instead - it\u0027ll statically link in libc++ as well, despite the name.\n\nFrom the Bazel\u0027s perspective, how do I configure the toolchain so that ALL `cc_binary`\u0027s built with this toolchain automatically has `libc++.so` included in runfiles?\n\nOr alternatively, should I always statically link in libc++ so that I don\u0027t need to add it to runfiles and to packaging?",
